projectDesc.p: ParlaMint is a project that aims to (1) create a multilingual set of comparable corpora of parliamentary proceedings uniformly encoded according to the ParlaMint encoding guidelines, covering the period from 2015 to mid-2022; (2) add linguistic annotations to the corpora and machine-translate them to English; (3) make the corpora available through concordancers; and (4) build use cases in Political Sciences and Digital Humanities based on the corpus data.

prefixDef.p: Private URIs with this prefix point to aligned source elements of the MTed corpus.

div.head: § 4 Meddelande om särskild debatt med anledning av rapporten från de säkerhetspolitiska överläggningarna
div.note: The Second Vice-President announced that, at the request of the Socialist Group, a special debate would take place on Monday 16 May at 2.30 p.m. on the report from the Security Policy Discussions. 10.30.
Prime Minister Magdalena Andersson (S) was to participate from the government.
The letter received was worded as follows:
Request for a special debate on Sweden's security policy
Russia's war against Ukraine has been condemned by Sweden and an almost united world. Sweden's strong solidarity with Ukraine stands firm.

In March, the Government initiated consultations with the parties of the Riksdag to discuss the changed state of security policy as a result of Russia's war. The deliberations involving all parties in the Riksdag shall analyse changes in the security policy situation resulting from Russia's aggression against Ukraine, including the consequences for Sweden's security policy, especially in relation to Sweden's international cooperation.

There is great value in the fact that the government and the parliamentary parties are discussing the major changes in security policy that Russian aggression brings. In this serious situation, it is important to carry out a thorough analysis of these issues. When the analysis is completed, it is extremely valuable if the parties of the Riksdag are given the opportunity to debate Sweden's security policy situation based on the analysis carried out.

In view of the presentation on 13 May of the Ministry letter from the Government's secure political deliberations with the parties of the Riksdag, the Social Democrats are asking for a special debate in the Riksdag.
